"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782071","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-06","<p>There are a total of 625 businesses that currently have a valid AEO status. The total in each of the nations of the UK are:</p><p> </p><p>534 - England</p><p>57 - Scotland</p><p>18 - Northern Ireland</p><p>16 - Wales</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-11-06T12:12:51.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782071/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782071/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782071/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-01","UK Trade with EU: Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many companies that have Authorised Economic Operator status are headquartered in each of the nations of the UK.","false","Biography information for Hannah Bardell","Livingston","Hannah Bardell","110856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782072","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-07","<p>HM Revenue and Customs are considering the capacity and capability requirements for future customs arrangements as part of their EU exit planning. This will be kept under review as negotiations progress.</p><p>The future customs controls required following EU exit will depend on the outcome of the negotiations. The Government will work to ensure that trade between the UK and the EU is as frictionless as possible.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-11-07T16:52:04.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782072/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782072/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782072/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-01","Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what preparations he has made to ensure skilled staff are in place for operation of customs arrangements on the day the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","110710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782073","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-08","<p>HM Treasury does not hold a central list of the IT and digital assets for all its arm’s length bodies.</p><p> </p><p>We do hold a list for the arm’s length bodies that use the Treasury’s shared IT service, these are UKGI, UKFI, NIC and GIAA.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-11-08T12:41:44.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782073/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782073/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782073/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-01","Treasury: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department holds a central list of the IT and digital assets of its arm's-length bodies.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","110736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782074","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-08","<p>The precise nature of our future relationship with the EU is still to be determined and is the subject of negotiation. The Government is working to secure a deal which achieves the freest possible trade in goods and services between the UK and the EU.</p><p><br> Discussion on the sanitary and phytosanitary conditions and related official controls that will be applicable to trade in animal and plant products will form part of these negotiations. Negotiations between the UK and the EU have so far been limited to the withdrawal arrangements. Like all Government departments, Defra is working on preparations for a range of scenarios to deliver a smooth departure from the EU.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-08T11:46:42.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782074/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782074/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782074/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-11-01","Borders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what preparations he is making to ensure sanitary and phytosanitary checks take place at the UK border on the day the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","110739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782075","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-07","<p>The Payment Scheme published a final report in November 2016 which set out the number of people who were issued payments. A copy can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/equitable-life-payment-scheme-final-report" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/equitable-life-payment-scheme-final-report</a>.</p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-11-07T14:11:02.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782075/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782075/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782075/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-01","Equitable Life Assurance Society: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of Equitable Life policyholders who have received payments of less than a quarter of their relative losses.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","110748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782076","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-07","<p>There are no scheduled meetings with the Equitable Members Action Group.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-11-07T14:09:10.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782076/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782076/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782076/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-01","Equitable Members Action Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he next plans to meet representatives of the Equitable Members' Action Group.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","110749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782077","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-07","<p>HM Treasury is working with all departments to understand the funding requirements to prepare for Brexit effectively. The additional funding HMRC has received for 2017-18 will be set out at Supplementary Estimates and funding for future years will be confirmed at a later date.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-11-07T15:39:05.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782077/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782077/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782077/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-01","Revenue and Customs: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much has been allocated to HM Revenue and Customs in percentage and cash terms on preparation for no deal being reached in negotiations on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Michael Tomlinson","Mid Dorset and North Poole","Michael Tomlinson","110751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782078","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-06","<p>The Valuation Office Agency (VOA)’s office in Rhyl will close during the 2019-20 financial year. The month of closure has not yet been announced.</p><p> </p><p>The VOA is committed to providing 12 months’ notice of any closures whenever possible, and will consult with staff affected by the closure of the Rhyl office and with trade unions.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-11-06T12:10:46.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782078/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782078/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782078/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-01","Valuation Office Agency: Rhyl","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans his Department has for the future of the Valuation Office in Rhyl.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","110776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782079","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-06","<p>The Government plans to publish supplementary Estimates for Government Departments in February 2018.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-11-06T15:23:00.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782079/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782079/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782079/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-01","Supply Estimates","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when his Department next plans to publish supplementary estimates for Government Departments.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","110778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782080","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-06","<p>Departments are preparing for a range of scenarios. To support these preparations, the Treasury has committed over £250m of additional spending in 2017-18 from the Reserve. Departmental allocations from the Reserve will be set out at Supplementary Estimates in the usual way.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-11-06T15:24:06.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782080/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782080/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782080/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-01","Government Departments: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what breakdown, by Department, of Government spending on contingencies for the UK leaving the EU he plans to include in the Budget red book.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","110779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782081","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-06","<p>We are helping people get a foot on the property ladder through a range of initiatives, including starter homes. Since spring 2010, Government-backed schemes have helped over 417,000 homes be purchased.</p><p>The precise definition of starter homes is being considered as part of the revised draft National Planning Policy Framework – until that definition is finalised no starter homes can be made available or sold.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","110544","2017-11-06T17:39:08.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782081/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782081/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782081/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-01","Housing: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many new starter homes have been built in (a) Coventry and (b) the West Midlands in each of the last two years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","110780"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782082","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-09","<p>The Department does not hold the information requested. Requirements on landlords to ensure their properties reach at least an Energy Performance Certificate rating of E before granting a new tenancy to new or existing tenants do not come into force until April 2018. The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy published an Impact Assessment on the impact of these proposals, which can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/401382/150202_PRS_Final_Stage_Revised_For_Publication.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/401382/150202_PRS_Final_Stage_Revised_For_Publication.pdf</a></p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-09T13:46:42.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782082/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782082/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782082/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-01","Private Rented Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 9 October 2017 to Question 105187, what information his Department holds on the number of private sector landlords who are complying with energy efficiency regulations on energy performance certificates.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","110744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782083","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-08","<p>My Department does not hold a central list of the IT and digital assets of its arm's-length bodies. This information is held by the individual arm's-length bodies.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-11-08T17:45:20.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782083/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782083/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782083/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-01","Department for Communities and Local Government: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether his Department holds a central list of the IT and digital assets of its arm's-length bodies.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","110721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782084","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-06","<p>The time taken to process an application for confirmation of a selective licensing will depend on the complexity of the case, whether the right information has been submitted with the application and whether the Department needs further clarification or additional details to help inform the decision.</p><p>The following schemes have been determined by the Secretary of State:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Local Authority </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Submission of Application </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Decision </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Peterborough City Council</p></td><td><p>23/03/2016</p></td><td><p>11/07/2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Burnley Borough Council</p></td><td><p>24/03/2016</p></td><td><p>11/07/2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London Borough of Redbridge</p></td><td><p>28/07/2015</p></td><td><p>18/12/2015</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-06T17:46:24.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782084/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782084/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782084/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-01","Private Rented Housing: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the length of time taken by his Department to determine each private rented sector selective licensing scheme application has been to date.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","110864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782085","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-06","<p>My Department has received applications from the following local authorities:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Local Authority </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Application Received by Department</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London Borough of Redbridge</p></td><td><p>28/07/2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Peterborough City Council</p></td><td><p>23/03/2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Burnley Borough Council</p></td><td><p>24/03/2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Blackpool Council</p></td><td><p>24/03/2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London Borough of Redbridge</p></td><td><p>04/07/2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London Borough of Newham</p></td><td><p>12/07/2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hyndburn Borough Council</p></td><td><p>12/07/2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London Borough of Brent</p></td><td><p>17/08/2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nottingham City Council</p></td><td><p>09/10/2017</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-06T17:45:45.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782085/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782085/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782085/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-01","Private Rented Housing: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, which local authorities have submitted applications for private rented sector selective licensing schemes; and on what date each such application was submitted.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","110865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782086","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-07","<p>The Department has considered the recommendations made by Eric Ollerenshaw in his review of local council tax support schemes. The Government response to the review’s findings will be published shortly.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-11-07T13:50:28.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782086/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782086/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782086/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-01","Local Council Tax Support Schemes Independent Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when his Department plans to publish its response to the Ollerenshaw Review of Local Council Tax Support Schemes (LCTS), published on 31 March 2016; and what steps he plans to take to better understand the effect of LCTS on individuals and councils.","false","Biography information for Yvonne Fovargue","Makerfield","Yvonne Fovargue","110889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782087","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-06","<p>The Department does not collect council tax data which identifies taxpayers under the age of 25.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-11-06T17:41:04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782087/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782087/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782087/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-01","Council Tax: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the level of council tax paid by care leavers under the age of 25.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","110956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782088","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-06","<p>The Government is committed to assisting care leavers. It has given councils the flexibility to support vulnerable groups, including care leavers, to help manage their council tax bills. We wrote to all councils in 2016 to remind them of the powers they had under the Local Government Finance Act 1992 to support vulnerable groups. A number of councils have already taken the decision to support care leavers through an exemption or discount on their council tax bills.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-11-06T17:41:31.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782088/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782088/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782088/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-01","Council Tax: Care Leavers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of exempting care leavers under the age of 25 from paying council tax.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","110957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782089","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-06","<p>We are assessing the options to renew the 2017 application deadline and will make an announcement in due course. To date the Better Broadband Scheme has provided access to basic broadband for over 10,000 premises. We will ensure that all premises continue to have access to basic broadband prior to the implementation of the Government's commitment that all premises have speeds of at least 10Mbps.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-11-06T16:36:05.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782089/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782089/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782089/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-11-01","Broadband: Business","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether the application deadline for the better broadband scheme is being extended beyond December 2017.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","110818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782090","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-09","<p>The information requested is not held centrally. <strong> </strong></p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-11-09T10:45:11.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782090/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782090/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782090/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-11-01","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether her Department holds a central list of the IT and digital assets of its arm's-length bodies.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","110723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782091","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-08","<p>We do not hold a central list of the IT and digital assets of the Ministry of Defence's arm's-length bodies. Under the delegated model, Senior Information Risk Owners, or an equivalent post, are appointed in each of the arm's-length bodies; they are expected to hold this information for their organisations in accordance with good practice. They report centrally on their organisation's key information systems as required.</p><p>Defence Assurance and Information Security (DAIS) also maintains the Defence Assurance Risk Tool (DART), an automated central registration point for MOD IT systems (including applications and services) that require accreditation. Users, including the arm's-length bodies, are required to comply with initiating, inputting to and tracking their various Information Assurance-related requirements on the DART to ensure that they are properly managed.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-08T16:10:45.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782091/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782091/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782091/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Ministry of Defence:ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department holds a central list of the IT and digital assets of its arm's-length bodies.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","110722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782092","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-08","<p>Further to the answer I gave the hon. Member on 16 October 2017 to Questions 106984, 106985, 106986 and 106987, the future location of the UK's M3 amphibious bridging capability remains subject to consideration, including deliberation on operational requirement, costs and discussions with Germany.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","110753 ; 110763 ; 110784","2017-11-08T15:36:46.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782092/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782092/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782092/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Amphibious Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answers of 16 October 2017 to Questions 106984, 106985, 106986 and 106987, how many M3 amphibious bridging vehicles are located in the UK; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","110752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782093","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-08","<p>Further to the answer I gave the hon. Member on 16 October 2017 to Questions 106984, 106985, 106986 and 106987, the future location of the UK's M3 amphibious bridging capability remains subject to consideration, including deliberation on operational requirement, costs and discussions with Germany.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","110752 ; 110753 ; 110784","2017-11-08T15:36:46.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782093/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782093/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782093/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Amphibious Vehicles: Germany","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answers of 16 October 2017 to Questions 106984, 106985, 106986 and 106987, if he will discuss with (a) his German counterpart and (b) German military command the feasibility of that country retaining and hosting either some or all of the 38 UK M3 amphibious bridging vehicles currently located in Germany following the final withdrawal of British forces in 2019; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","110763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782094","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-08","<p>Further to the answer I gave the hon. Member on 16 October 2017 to Questions 106984, 106985, 106986 and 106987, the future location of the UK's M3 amphibious bridging capability remains subject to consideration, including deliberation on operational requirement, costs and discussions with Germany.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","110752 ; 110763 ; 110784","2017-11-08T15:36:46.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782094/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782094/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782094/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Amphibious Vehicles: Germany","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answers of 16 October 2017 to Questions 106984, 106985, 106986 and 106987, if he will detail the estimated cost of relocating the 38 UK M3 amphibious bridging vehicles that are currently located in Germany back to the UK; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","110753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782095","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-08","<p>Further to the answer I gave the hon. Member on 16 October 2017 to Questions 106984, 106985, 106986 and 106987, the future location of the UK's M3 amphibious bridging capability remains subject to consideration, including deliberation on operational requirement, costs and discussions with Germany.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","110752 ; 110753 ; 110763","2017-11-08T15:36:46.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782095/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782095/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782095/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Amphibious Vehicles: Germany","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answers of 16 October 2017 to Questions 106984, 106985, 106986 and 106987, whether 38 UK M3 amphibious bridging vehicles have been located in Germany during 2017; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","110784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782096","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-06","<p>A copy of Defence Instruction Notice 2016DIN01-052 titled 'Assisted Conception and Fertility Policy' has been placed in the Library of the House.</p><p>The Chain of Command provides regular reminders of the availability of Fertility Preservation (FP) to Service personnel. In addition, an awareness campaign promoting the benefits of FP has been undertaken including an intranet awareness campaign and magazine and newspaper articles for the Family Federations and each of the Services to ensure that maximum coverage was achieved.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-06T16:42:04.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782096/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782096/answer","Defence Instruction Notice 2016DIN01-052 titled Assisted Conception and Fertility Policy (1).pdf","110783 - Conception and Fertility Policy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782096/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Armed Forces: Fertility","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place copies in the Library of the advice and guidance his Department provides to members of the armed forces on sperm and egg banking during service; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","110783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782097","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-06","<p>The Ministry of Defence has published the &quot;Purple Pack&quot;, which provides guidance for Service families through the practical elements of bereavement whilst also providing links to further support networks. I have placed a copy in the Library of the House.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-06T16:42:34.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782097/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782097/answer","20170511_Purple_Pack.pdf","110795 - MODs "Purple Pack"","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782097/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Armed Forces: Bereavement Counselling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place a copy in the Library of the latest guidance and procedure for communications with and supporting bereaved relatives of members of the armed forces; and if he will make statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","110795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782098","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-08","<p>The names for the new City Class Type 26 Frigates have been decided and will be announced at appropriate opportunities in the future. So far two ships have been named as HMS GLASGOW and HMS BELFAST</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-08T16:27:42.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782098/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782098/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782098/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Type 23 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will name one of the Royal Navy's next generation of Type 26 frigates after the city of Sheffield.","false","Biography information for Jared O'Mara","Sheffield, Hallam","Jared O'Mara","110824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782099","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-06","<p>The Royal Navy continually reviews their requirements for future waterfront infrastructure, including berths, docks and related facilities, to inform decisions regarding infrastructure investment, base porting and maintenance. No such decisions have been made regarding HMS RICHMOND.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-06T17:41:03.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782099/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782099/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782099/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","HMS Richmond","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to move HMS Richmond's base port from Portsmouth to Devonport.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","110817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782100","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-06","<p>The potential sale of HMS OCEAN has been discussed with both the Government of Brazil and the Government of Chile.</p><p>There have been no such discussions with either Government in respect of HMS ALBION, HMS BULWARK or in-service Type 23 frigates.</p><p>We sold three Type 23 frigates to Chile in 2006.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-06T17:40:30.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782100/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782100/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782100/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Warships: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department has had any discussions with the Governments of Chile or Brazil on the purchase of (a) HMS Ocean, (b) HMS Albion, (c) HMS Bulwark and (d) any Type 23 frigate.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","110854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782101","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-08","<p>The cost to the Ministry of Defence of commercial vehicle leasing and hire for the last five financial years (FY) is:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>FY 2016-17</p></td><td><p>FY 2015-16</p></td><td><p>FY 2014-15</p></td><td><p>FY 2013-14</p></td><td><p>FY 2012-13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£107.2 million</p></td><td><p>£124.1 million</p></td><td><p>£132.4 million</p></td><td><p>£125.5 million</p></td><td><p>£101.9 million</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-08T16:21:07.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782101/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782101/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782101/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Armed Forces: Motor Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the value was of commercial civilian vehicle leasing and hire contracts with his Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","110890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782102","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-08","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not hold claims information separately for incidents involving lease/hire vehicles. The number of third party motor claims received by the Department arising from the activities of visiting forces in the last five years is shown below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Calendar Year</p></td><td><p>Number of Third Party Motor Claims Received</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>29</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>29</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>19</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>28</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>123</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-08T16:00:22.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782102/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782102/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782102/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Armed Forces: Motor Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many vehicles hired or leased by his Department driven by visiting forces have received damage that led to an insurance claim in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","110891"
