"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782273","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-08","<p>The 59 instances the Report refers to are the National Audit Office's calculations of the average level of the redistribution of parts across the Astute Class submarine fleet. The costs of in-service support for the submarine fleet are not captured in the format requested.</p><p>Across the Maritime Domain work is under way to deliver improved effective and efficient support. The Royal Navy will use the information from the Report to monitor trends more closely and review the impact of cost saving decisions to inform their through life management approach.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","110914","2017-11-08T16:01:17.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782273/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782273/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782273/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Submarines: Spare Parts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to reduce the amount of cannibalisation involving Astute Class submarines.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","110919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782274","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-06","<p>All Service personnel are entitled to Service Family Accommodation at Decent Homes Standard or above. No Service family are obligated to accept a home below this standard.</p><p>Of the properties assessed 96% are now at or exceed the Decent Homes Standard.</p><p>The vast majority of properties below decent homes standard are vacant and will not to be allocated to Service families. A very small minority are large listed buildings which nevertheless fall under the category of Service Family Accommodation.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-06T17:42:31.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782274/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782274/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782274/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-01","Armed Forces: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 13 March to Question 66809, what steps the Government has taken to ensure that the six per cent of service accommodation properties below the decent homes standard improve to meet that standard.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","110950"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782275","Department for Education","false","2017-11-06","<p>The Student Loans Company (SLC) has confirmed that its Acting Chief Executive wrote to the hon. Member for Christchurch on 31 October providing a substantive response to his complaint in line with published timescales.</p><p>The SLC has also confirmed that it wrote to the customer concerned on the same date confirming that, in line with its complaints procedure, their complaint has been escalated to Independent Assessor review stage</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-11-06T17:36:59.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782275/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782275/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782275/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-01","Student Loans Company: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when the Acting Chief Executive of the Student Loans Company Ltd will give a substantive reply to the complaint on behalf of Customer 67178459697 made by the hon. Member for Christchurch.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","110953"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782276","Department for Education","false","2017-11-08","<p>Based on the 2016-17 financial year, the total adult education budget was £1.5billion. Our latest annual accounts for the financial year 2016-17 show an underspend of £15million, or 1 per cent, at year end.</p><p> </p><p>Providers were allocated funds based on the previous year, so no bids were received.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-11-08T18:50:10.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782276/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782276/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782276/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-01","Adult Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much of the adult education budget was spent last year; and how many bids were received for that grant.","false","Biography information for Jared O'Mara","Sheffield, Hallam","Jared O'Mara","110887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782277","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-07","<p>As announced on 30 September, a bill to increase the maximum penalties for animal cruelty will be available for comment around the turn of the year. It has not been decided what form of consultation will be undertaken.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-07T17:53:56.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782277/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782277/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782277/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-11-01","Animal Welfare: Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will consult (a) Battersea Dogs and Cats Home and (b) other animal welfare charities before publishing the draft legislation to increase sentences for animal cruelty for wider consultation.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","110929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782278","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-06","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer that I gave to the hon. Member for Easington (Grahame Morris), on 20 October 2017, PQ UIN 107863.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-11-06T11:57:17.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782278/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782278/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782278/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-11-01","Food: Plastics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether he plans to take steps to limit the use of single-use plastics within the retail food industry.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","110931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782279","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-06","<p>The Government is committed to improving the welfare of all animals. The Government has always been clear that it would prefer animals to be slaughtered close to the point of production. Our manifesto made it clear that we would take early steps to control the export of live farm animals for slaughter once we leave the European Union.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-06T14:22:53.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782279/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782279/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782279/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-11-01","Livestock: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what specific measures he will introduce to prevent the export of live animals for slaughter after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","110951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782280","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-06","<p>We hope to publish draft legislation for consultation around the turn of the year, as announced on 30 September.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-06T14:21:15.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782280/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782280/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782280/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-11-01","Animal Welfare: Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when he plans to introduce legislation to increase the maximum sentence for animal cruelty offences to five years imprisonment.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","110952"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782281","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-06","<p>We hope to publish draft legislation for consultation around the turn of the year, as announced on 30 September.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-06T14:17:34.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782281/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782281/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782281/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-11-01","Animal Welfare: Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when he plans to publish the draft bill to increase animal cruelty sentences ahead of the planned consultation.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","110928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782282","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-08","<p>We have just commenced a review of the UK Food Security Assessment. The Food Security Assessment analyses the different national and global factors impacting on UK food supply. It is a comprehensive piece of work, covering all aspects of food security, including UK household food security. The Government has committed to reviewing this assessment.</p><p>The annual ONS Living Costs and Food Survey (LCFS) includes questions on household spend on food, including that of the lowest 20% income households, which has remained constant between 16% and 16.5% for a number of years.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-08T17:08:16.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782282/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782282/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782282/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-11-01","Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what progress has been made on the UK Food Security Assessment; and if he will make it his policy to measure and monitor household food insecurity in the UK more regularly.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","110923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782283","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-08","<p>The ONS Living Costs and Food Survey (LCFS) includes questions on household spend on food, including that of the lowest 20% income households, which has remained constant between 16% and 16.5% for a number of years</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-08T17:05:45.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782283/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782283/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782283/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-11-01","Food: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to assess the effect of the recent rise in food prices on the level of food insecurity in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","110924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782284","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-07","<p>Bees and other pollinators play an essential role in our £100 billion food industry. In 2014, Defra published an independent review of the evidence on the status and value of pollinators. The review estimated that pollinators added approximately £600 million per year to the value of UK crops through increased yield in oil seed rape and various fruit and vegetables.</p><p> </p><p>The review identified an overall decline in wild and honey bees over the past 50 years highlighting the potential future risk to the yield or quality of UK crops, and recommending future research.</p><p> </p><p>The research evidence base on pollinators and pollination is constantly improving and we keep this under review through our expert advisory groups. We are also taking action both to understand better any future risks and to mitigate them. In collaboration with research institutes, the Devolved Administrations and volunteer organisations, we have established a pollinator monitoring and research partnership to gather further data and improve our understanding of the status of pollinators and pollination services in the UK. We have also introduced a Pollinator and Wildlife Package to our Countryside Stewardship Scheme in England, and are working with farmers, business and conservation organisations to provide pollinator habitat on farmland, in urban areas and in gardens in order to boost pollinator populations.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-07T18:00:00.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782284/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782284/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782284/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-11-01","Bees: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the future of UK agriculture without a healthy bee population.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","110987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782285","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-06","<p>The department has mechanisms in place to monitor the effectiveness of spending to combat the illegal wildlife trade. All illegal wildlife trade grants have to report on what they have achieved with the money allocated to them, and have an agreed monitoring and evaluation plan and targets. Illegal Wildlife Trade Challenge Fund projects submit six-monthly, annual and final reports on their progress. The annual and final reports are reviewed by an independent assessor.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-11-06T11:53:42.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782285/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782285/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782285/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-11-01","Nature Conservation: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 31 October 2017 to Question 109459, on Africa: poaching, what steps his Department has taken to monitor the effectiveness of spending to combat the illegal wildlife trade.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","110961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782286","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-07","<p>The UK continues to express strong ​​concerns about human rights and freedoms in Tibet. We consistently urge the Chinese authorities to respect all fundamental rights across the People's Republic of China, in line with both its own constitution and the international frameworks to which it is a party.</p><p>We raised our concerns about Tibet directly with the Chinese authorities at the UK-China Human Rights Dialogue held in Beijing on 27 June.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-11-07T17:55:30.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782286/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782286/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782286/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-01","Tibet: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to raise concerns on human rights abuses in Tibet directly with Xi Jinping.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","110967"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782287","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>​The UK is commmitted to strengthening the links between the Commonwealth. However, the only category of Commonwealth membership is that of sovereign states. The UK will discuss the policy priorities for the Heads of Government Meeting with the Overseas Territories ahead of next April and represent them at the summit.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-11-06T17:53:44.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782287/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782287/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782287/answer","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782287/answer/previousversion/20508","Biography information for Alistair Burt","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-01","British Overseas Territories: Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he plans to offer observer status to the British Overseas Territories during the Commonwealth Summit in London in April 2018.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","110962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782288","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>We remain deeply concerned by the violence in the Central African Republic. The fact that the unrest has spread to locations and communities, such as Boda, which were previously relatively untouched is particularly troubling. In our position as a member of the UN Security Council we are committed to ensuring that the United Nations peacekeeping mission (MINUSCA) has the tools to provide effective protection for civilians, specifically the most vulnerable, such as women and children.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-11-06T15:58:16.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782288/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782288/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782288/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-01","Central African Republic: Religious Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what support his Department is providing to the women of Boda, Central African Republic, and their mission for an end to violence between Christians and Muslims in that region.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","110904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782289","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>Ricardo Palmera, also known as Simón Trinidad, is a Colombian citizen extradited to, and sentenced in, the United States of America. His status as a US prisoner is a bilateral issue between Colombia and the United States. There are currently no plans to meet his legal representatives.</p><p>We welcome the significant progress made in the peace process, including the FARC's laying down of arms.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-11-06T13:42:51.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782289/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782289/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782289/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-01","Colombia: Peace Negotiations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the significance of Simon Trinidad to the peace and reconciliation process in Colombia.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","110938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782290","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>Ricardo Palmera, also known as Simón Trinidad, is a Colombian citizen extradited to, and sentenced in, the United States of America. His status as a US prisoner is a bilateral issue between Colombia and the United States. There are currently no plans to meet his legal representatives.</p><p>We welcome the significant progress made in the peace process, including the FARC's laying down of arms.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-11-06T13:47:46.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782290/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782290/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782290/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-01","Simon Trinidad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to his US counterpart to ask for the repatriation of Simon Trinidad.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","110939"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782291","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-08","<p>Sudan remains a Human Rights Priority Country for the Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office, and civil society and freedom of expression are among our key human rights concerns.</p><p>We used the fourth round of the UK-Sudan Strategic Dialogue on 16 October to agree steps that the Government of Sudan would take to make further progress on human rights issues, including civil society and freedom of expression, particularly in the run up to elections in 2020.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-11-08T15:24:43.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782291/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782291/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782291/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-01","Sudan: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assurance he has received from the Government of Sudan on the protection of civil society activists during the round of the UK-Sudan Strategic Dialogue on 16 October 2017.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Sir Henry Bellingham","110884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782292","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>Ricardo Palmera, also known as Simón Trinidad, is a Colombian citizen extradited to, and sentenced in, the United States of America. His status as a US prisoner is a bilateral issue between Colombia and the United States. There are currently no plans to meet his legal representatives.</p><p>We welcome the significant progress made in the peace process, including the FARC's laying down of arms.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-11-06T13:41:16.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782292/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782292/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782292/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-01","Simon Trinidad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will meet the American legal representative of Simon Trinidad.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","110937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782293","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-08","<p><strong>​</strong>A communiqué outlining the progress made during the fourth round of the UK-Sudan Strategic Dialogue was published on 1 November, and is now available on the UK Government’s website.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-11-08T15:22:52.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782293/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782293/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782293/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-01","Sudan: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether his Department plans to publish a public document outlining the progress made during the round of the UK-Sudan Strategic Dialogue on 16 October 2017.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Sir Henry Bellingham","110883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782294","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>We continue to offer consular support to Mr Tsege and his family. We previously secured Mr Tsege’s transfer from solitary confinement to a federal prison and access to a lawyer. Officials have visited Mr Tsege 18 times, most recently on 12 October, when they were able to check on his welfare, discuss his legal access and pass on messages from his family.</p><p>In addition, the Prime Minister and the Foreign Secretary raised Mr Tsege’s case with Ethiopia’s Prime Minister and Foreign Minister in May. The Minister for Africa met with Mr Tsege's family on 24 October, and also raised the case during his visit to Ethiopia in August. Our Ambassador takes every opportunity to raise Mr Tsege’s case at the highest levels with the Ethiopian Government.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-11-06T16:01:46.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782294/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782294/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782294/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-01","Andargachew Tsege","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent progress has been made in securing the release of Andy Tsege.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","110933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782295","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-08","<p>The creation of safe, legal migration pathways for Sudanese migrants was not a topic of discussion at the fourth round of the Strategic Dialogue on 16 October.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-11-08T15:26:20.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782295/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782295/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782295/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-01","Sudan: Migration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the creation of safe, legal migration pathways for Sudanese migrants was discussed in the round of the UK-Sudan Strategic Dialogue on 16 October 2017.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Sir Henry Bellingham","110885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782296","Department of Health","false","2017-11-08","<p>The final report of the Mesh Oversight Group led by NHS England sets out the action that is being taken to improve awareness of complications, to ensure the consent process for patients is strengthened and to put in place access to additional care and support where needed. The Government will continue to work with the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency to ensure that the potential complications of these devices are better understood and that any necessary action is taken.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-11-08T17:33:13.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782296/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782296/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782296/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-01","Surgical Mesh Implants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department plans to take to assist people affected by failed mesh implants; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","110882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782297","Department of Health","false","2017-11-07","<p>The Department does not collect data on the number of National Health Service workers leaving their position due to stress. Employers across the NHS are responsible for the physical and mental health and wellbeing of their staff.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Trusts are being supported to improve their staff mental health and reduce their stress through NHS England’s “Commissioning for Quality and Innovation” incentive scheme which is encouraging trusts to provide quick access to mental health support services including, for example, mindfulness apps and mental health talking therapies.</p><p>The recently published ‘Stepping forward to 2020/21: The mental health workforce plan for England<sup>1</sup> recognises the need to support NHS staff. The plan proposes that the Paul Farmer and Lord Stevenson review of mental health and employers – ‘Thriving at Work<sup>2</sup>’ should form the basis for Board discussions about how NHS organisations can better support their own staff and increase awareness around mental health issues amongst the workforce. The expectation is that all the recommendations within the mental health workforce plan will be implemented by 2020/21.</p><p> </p><p>The Department continues to commission NHS Employers to support the NHS in improving staff health and wellbeing through advice, guidance and good practice including, for example, their ‘How are you feeling NHS? Toolkit<sup>3</sup>’ which should help staff check their own emotional wellbeing or speak to and support colleagues with theirs.</p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p> </p><p><sup>1</sup><a href="https://www.hee.nhs.uk/our-work/person-centred-care/mental-health/mental-health-workforce-plan" target="_blank">https://www.hee.nhs.uk/our-work/person-centred-care/mental-health/mental-health-workforce-plan</a></p><p><sup> </sup></p><p><sup>2</sup><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/thriving-at-work-a-review-of-mental-health-and-employers" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/thriving-at-work-a-review-of-mental-health-and-employers</a></p><p><sup> </sup></p><p><sup>3</sup><a href="http://www.nhsemployers.org/howareyoufeelingnhs" target="_blank">http://www.nhsemployers.org/howareyoufeelingnhs</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-11-07T15:20:05.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782297/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782297/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782297/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-01","NHS: Resignations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many NHS workers left their positions due to workplace stress in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","110880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782298","Department of Health","false","2017-11-08","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>The General Medical Council advises, in their publication ‘Good Medical Practice’ that doctors must explain to patients if they have a conscientious objection to a particular procedure. Doctors must tell patients about their right to see another doctor and make sure they have enough information to exercise that right to arrange to see another doctor who does not hold the same objection.</p><p>The guidance also advises that, if it is not practical for a patient to arrange to see another doctor, arrangements should be made – without delay – for another suitably qualified colleague to advise, treat or refer the patient. Doctors must bear in mind the patient’s vulnerability and act promptly to make sure they are not denied appropriate treatment or services.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","110874","2017-11-08T17:12:56.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782298/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782298/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782298/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-01","Contraceptives","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the cost to the NHS of rebooking appointments as a result of a refusal to prescribe the  contraceptive pill due to a conscientious objection.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","110878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782299","Department of Health","false","2017-11-08","<p>The Government recognises the pressures that National Health Service staff are under and is proposing to improve the working environment for NHS staff by offering more flexible working, improving staff health and wellbeing, tackling bullying and violence against NHS staff. This will complement the work ongoing across the NHS, championed by NHS England, to ensure staff have a better working environment.</p><p> </p><p>The Department uses staff engagement as a proxy for measuring NHS staff morale and the 2016 NHS Staff Survey showed an improvement in the overall engagement score for the NHS. This score combines staff recommending their organisation as a place to work or receive treatment, staff motivation at work and how much staff are able to contribute towards improvement at work.</p><p> </p><p>NHS Employers is also working with NHS England and Public Health England on NHS England’s initiative[1] to improve staff health and wellbeing which includes a “CQUIN”[2] (Commissioning for Quality and Innovation), a new three part indicator focussing on getting staff better access to health and wellbeing initiatives, supporting them to make healthy choices and lead healthy lives.</p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p> </p><p><sup>1</sup><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/2015/09/improving-staff-health/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/2015/09/improving-staff-health/</a></p><p> </p><p><sup>2</sup><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cquin-guidance-16-17-v3.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cquin-guidance-16-17-v3.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-11-08T10:55:35.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782299/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782299/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782299/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-01","NHS: Working Conditions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to (a) monitor and (b) improve the work environment of NHS Workers.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","110879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782300","Department of Health","false","2017-11-08","<p>Each of the organisations contained within Sussex and East Surrey’s Sustainability and Transformation Partnership (STP), is engaging staff, patients, local residents and stakeholder groups around their joint plans.</p><p> </p><p>The STP has decided that their preferred approach is to develop four 'place based plans' within their STP: Coastal Care, East Sussex Better Together and the North and South parts of the Central Sussex and East Surrey Alliance. They are undertaking public and patient engagement on that basis. Details of all engagement events they have held can be reviewed on the individual partner websites.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the partners are also establishing an STP wide patient and public engagement steering group to help shape and improve STP-wide engagement.</p><p> </p><p>The STP Dashboard was published in July to provide an initial baseline view of STP performance. Upon publication, Sussex and East Surrey STP were rated in ‘Category 4- Needs Most Improvement’. NHS England intends to update the dashboard annually to enable progress to be tracked, and outcomes to be measured. The STP dashboard can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/11-pb-21-07-2017-stp-progress-dashboard.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/11-pb-21-07-2017-stp-progress-dashboard.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>STP partners have established a pooled fund to support the work of the STP. The total spend from March 2016 to end of September 2017 was £2,264,000. This figure is inclusive of consultancy and reviews.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has not made an assessment of the potential merits of redrawing the geographical scope of the STP – however, NHS England has set out arrangements for STPs to be able to propose an adjustment to their geographical boundaries. The geographical scope and composition of Sussex and East Surrey STP is a matter for its local partners.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","110980 ; 110981 ; 110989","2017-11-08T17:16:59.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782300/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782300/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782300/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-01","Sustainability and Transformation Partnerships: East Surrey and Sussex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what engagement events have been undertaken by the Sussex and East Surrey Sustainability and Transformation Partnership with local stakeholders since that partnership was set up.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","110990"
