"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782302","Department of Health","false","2017-11-06","<p>As at April 2017, all police forces in England had access to mental health support and advice for their officers when dealing with members of the public who appear to be suffering with mental ill health. 38 out of 40 police forces had a recognised Street Triage type model, the remaining two forces had local agreements for support from mental health trusts to meet their requirements.</p><p> </p><p>The hours of support offered by each police force area is determined at a local level according to demand and needs of the service.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","110848","2017-11-06T16:23:54.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782302/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782302/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782302/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-01","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will list the areas in which street triage schemes for mental health policing are in operation.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","110847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782303","Department of Health","false","2017-11-06","<p>As at April 2017, all police forces in England had access to mental health support and advice for their officers when dealing with members of the public who appear to be suffering with mental ill health. 38 out of 40 police forces had a recognised Street Triage type model, the remaining two forces had local agreements for support from mental health trusts to meet their requirements.</p><p> </p><p>The hours of support offered by each police force area is determined at a local level according to demand and needs of the service.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","110847","2017-11-06T16:23:54.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782303/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782303/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782303/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-01","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, which areas that operated a street triage scheme for mental health policing operated 24 hours a day.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","110848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782304","Department of Health","false","2017-11-07","<p>In February 2016, the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) published a refreshed clinical guideline 72: Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder: diagnosis and management. This sets out the evidence-based approach to supporting children over three, young people and adults with attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD).</p><p> </p><p>NICE is developing a new guideline on ADHD which is expected to be published in February 2018.</p><p> </p><p>England continues to develop pathways for mental health services, which benefit people with ADHD needing mental health support, to promote evidence-based approaches to care and tackle unwarranted variation in provision. NICE and the National Collaborating Centre for Mental Health have been commissioned to develop these pathways.</p><p> </p><p>Information on waiting times for ADHD diagnosis, or on the waiting time from referral to treatment, is not collected centrally by the National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>Information on funding specifically allocated to ADHD treatment by local commissioners in the last seven years is not held centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","110870 ; 110873","2017-11-07T15:23:17.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782304/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782304/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/782304/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-01","Hyperactivity: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what funding his Department has allocated to ADHD treatment in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","110871"
